  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (adversarial: inconsistent requirements)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: package binds two requirement nodes whose acceptance thresholds are mutually exclusive when evaluated at the COU operating point — one mandates RH < 1.0 as the sole pass criterion, while the other requires RH ≤ 1.05 AND forbids any RH value below 0.95 on grounds of physiological implausibility, thereby prohibiting the very RH range that the first requirement demands.",
