      "type": "Requirement",
      "name": "Primary RH acceptance criterion",
      "specification": "The CFD model shall be considered validated for CPB hemolysis prediction if and only if the computed Relative Hemolysis index (RH) satisfies RH < 1.0 across all five evaluated flow-speed operating points. Any single operating point yielding RH ≥ 1.0 constitutes a failure of the acceptance criterion and invalidates the model for the stated COU. This threshold is unconditional and applies regardless of experimental uncertainty bounds.",
      "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-physiological-plausibility-criterion",
      "type": "Requirement",
      "name": "Physiological plausibility bounding requirement",
      "specification": "To ensure physiological plausibility of the hemolysis model, all computed RH values must fall within the interval [0.95, 1.05] relative to the predicate device reference. RH values below 0.95 are prohibited as they indicate non-physical suppression of hemolysis prediction and shall be treated as model failure requiring recalibration. This requirement is co-equal in precedence to any other acceptance criterion applied to the same claim.",
      "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification"
    }
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to evaluate the sensitivity of pump-induced hemolysis to variations in component dimensions for a centrifugal blood pump used during cardiopulmonary bypass surgery. Model influence is MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect tolerance decision could impact clinical hemolysis levels). Model Risk Level 2.",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
