    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 with adequate mitigations documented. Computed RH values range from 0.91 to 0.98, satisfying the primary acceptance criterion RH < 1.0 across all five operating points. The model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The assessment team noted the secondary physiological plausibility requirement (RH ≥ 0.95 lower bound) but concluded the primary criterion governs the accept/reject decision for regulatory submission purposes.",
